<text>Loading External Scripts from a File

&lt; Back &gt;


Syntax:

external [filename.mws]

The following example shows the communication between two models, and a model and a text box, using the above command.

  
  
   

The external block should in general be favored, because the scripts will be saved when the page gets saved. Only when the scripts become very lengthy should you consider putting them in separate files.

